Hardware Required

✅ Netgate 1100 (or compatible pfSense appliance)
✅ TP-Link TL-SG108E managed switch (or 802.1Q compatible)
✅ TP-Link EAP225 access point (or VLAN-capable AP)
✅ Starlink dish with ethernet adapter (or WAN connection)
✅ Ethernet cables (Cat5e/Cat6) - minimum 4 cables
✅ Computer for initial configuration
Knowledge Required

Basic networking concepts (IP addressing, subnets)
Understanding of VLANs and 802.1Q tagging
Familiarity with web-based administration
Basic command line skills (helpful but not required)
Before You Begin

 Download latest pfSense version (verify checksum)
 Have credentials ready (you'll set admin password)
 Plan your IP addressing scheme
 Print network diagram and port mapping sheet
 Clear workspace and label your cables
